==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*fallanan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[falla]], Old Saxon [[fallan]] (Dutch [[vallen]]), Old High German [[fallan]] (German [[fallen]]), Old Norse [[falla]] (Swedish [[falla]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈfæalːan/}}

===Verb===
'''feallan''' (class VII strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[fielþ]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[feoll|fēoll]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[feollon|fēollon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[feallen]]''')
# to [[fall]], fall down

